steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"913ch","text":"When MEF-cultured hPSCs reach 50% confluency, change medium to hPSCs medium + Rock inhibitor, preparing for nucleofection the next day. For each 20 µl nucleofection reaction, prepare half to 1 well of cells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"72fdj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9iol0","text":"A detailed protocol on maintaining MEF-cultured hPSCs can be found in the collection \"Maintenance and inactivation of mouse embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) as feeder cells for human pluripotent stem cell culture;\" dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4pbqvin","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"egrq9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9cbdo","text":"Prepare feeder plate at least 1 day earlier as depicted in the collection \"Maintenance and inactivation of mouse embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) as feeder cell for human pluripotent stem cell culture,\" dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4pbqvin","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f8eid","text":"Incubate    . Watch for edge curling of the colonies as indication collagenase incubation is complete.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":9,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":10,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ddgdb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5mk6c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":1800,"guid":"168926307E1611ECB9C2DBB408B99C21","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}},"1":{"type":"temperature","mutability":"","data":{"error_temperature":false,"guid":"1C7591507E1611ECB9C2DBB408B99C21","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"temperature":"37","unit":10}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dmnvr","text":"Pipette repeatedly with 5 ml pipette to lift colonies, careful not to carry over too many MEFs.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"k9ui","text":"Resuspend cell pellet in 1 ml DMEM/F12, triturate to single cells using P1000 tips","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8f2k0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8c710","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3pts8","text":"Take two 10 µl sets of the cell suspension.. Mix each set with 10 µl trypan blue dye which comes with the Countess™ Cell Counting Chamber Slides","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"STRIKETHROUGH","offset":42,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dqdo8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ff11s","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2pjfu","text":"Count cells with Countess automated cell counter or hemocytometer, average the counts from the two sets. Continue with re-suspending the cell pellet in 20 ml nucleofection solution as described in the protocol \"Nucleofection of hPSCs\" (Step 2)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6iojp","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d7rte","text":"The protocol \"Nucleofection of hPSCs\" can be found in the collection \"Nucleofection (Amaxa) and electroporation (Biorad) of hPSCs.\" A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eqq2j","text":"Mix the cell suspension in the conical tube, take 500,000 cells per nucleofection reaction and transfer to a new conical tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5hvtm","text":"Aspirate supernatant as much as possible, to minimize the interference to the nucleofection buffer system.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
